      "writtenOn": "2026-07-10T09:39:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This call doesn\u0027t make sense to me, because the `runIndexTaskSynchronously` does:\n\n1. Set the forwarded context\n2. Lock the `id` passed as a parameter\n3. Run the lambda synchronously\n\nThe `id` here isn\u0027t relevant because the action will remove all changes for a project, and it won\u0027t be on a single change ID.\n\nThe only useful thing is the forwarded context for avoiding the loop of events.",
